---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";

const title = "Privacy policy";
const description = "Privacy policy";
---

<Base title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/privacy-policy">
  <Section>
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        The controller of your personal data is Content Bytes Foundation, based
        in Kraków, Poland.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy or the
        processing of your personal data, you can contact us at:
        hello@contentbytes.pl.
      </p>
      <h2>2. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        In connection with ticket sales, we may process the following personal
        data:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>first and last name</li>
        <li>email address</li>
        <li>phone number (if provided)</li>
        <li>information related to the purchase of a ticket</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Payment information is processed by Stripe, our third-party payment
        service provider.
      </p>
      <h2>3. Purposes and Legal Bases for Processing</h2>
      <p>We process personal data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          to sell and deliver tickets and manage your order, pursuant to Article
          6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of a contract)
        </li>
        <li>
          to comply with legal obligations, including accounting and tax
          requirements, pursuant to Article 6(1)(c) GDPR
        </li>
        <li>
          to establish, exercise, or defend legal claims, pursuant to Article
          6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interests of the Controller)
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We may also process participants’ images captured in photographs and/or
        video recordings taken during the Event. Such materials may be used for
        documentation and promotional purposes related to the Organizer’s
        activities, including publication on websites, social media channels,
        and other marketing materials. This processing is based on the
        Controller’s legitimate interest pursuant to Article 6(1)(f) GDPR.
      </p>
      <h2>4. Data Recipients</h2>
      <p>
        Your personal data may be shared with service providers supporting the
        ticket sales process, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Naffy (ticketing and registration platform)</li>
        <li>Stripe (payment processing provider)</li>
        <li>
          accounting, IT, and hosting service providers, where necessary for the
          purposes described above
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain personal data for as long as necessary to perform the contract
        and fulfill our legal obligations, including obligations arising from
        tax and accounting laws.
      </p>
      <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under the GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>access your personal data</li>
        <li>rectify inaccurate personal data</li>
        <li>request the erasure of your personal data</li>
        <li>request restriction of processing</li>
        <li>object to processing where permitted by law</li>
        <li>
          receive your personal data in a portable format where applicable
        </li>
        <li>lodge a complaint with the competent data protection authority</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>7. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Some service providers, including Stripe, may process personal data
        outside the European Economic Area (EEA). In such cases, personal data
        is transferred in accordance with GDPR requirements and subject to
        appropriate safeguards.
      </p>
      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions regarding the processing of your personal
        data, please contact us at: hello@contentbytes.pl.
      </p>
    </article>
  </Section>
</Base>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    color: white;
  }
</style>